#-------------------------------------------------------------------
# Synthetic P 1 orthorhombic test case for the Xtalate CIF parser (M20).
#
# Promoted from the real-world corpus: the two defects the COD batch found
# (a misleading occupancy warning, and cell-parameter precision loss that was
# reported nowhere) are pinned here in a form small enough to verify by hand.
#
# Orthorhombic with all angles 90 makes fractional -> Cartesian exact and
# trivial: x_cart = x_frac * a, and likewise for b and c.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------
data_occupancy_cell_uncertainty
_chemical_name_common          'Xtalate M20 synthetic occupancy/uncertainty test'
_chemical_formula_sum          'Na Cl2'
_cell_length_a                 4.0000(3)
_cell_length_b                 5.0000(2)
_cell_length_c                 6.0000(1)
_cell_angle_alpha              90.0
_cell_angle_beta               90.0
_cell_angle_gamma              90.0
_space_group_name_H-M_alt      'P 1'
_space_group_IT_number         1
loop_
_space_group_symop_operation_xyz
'x, y, z'
loop_
_atom_site_label
_atom_site_type_symbol
_atom_site_fract_x
_atom_site_fract_y
_atom_site_fract_z
_atom_site_occupancy
Na1  Na  0.0000000000  0.0000000000  0.0000000000  1.000
Cl1  Cl  0.5000000000  0.5000000000  0.5000000000  0.500
Cl2  Cl  0.5000000000  0.0000000000  0.0000000000  ?
